          "interaction_type": "crack deflection and blunting at carbide/ferrite lamellae",
          "quality_description": "Cracks propagating in δ-ferrite lamellae are arrested and blunted at carbide/ferrite interfaces; carbides increase effective crack tip curvature radius, reducing stress concentration."
        },
        {
          "interaction_id": "def_int_R650_02",
          "microstructure_uuid": "micro_R650_CF",
          "interaction_type": "microvoid nucleation at carbide/ferrite interfaces",
          "quality_description": "Spherical carbides act as nucleation sites for microvoids, inducing horizontal crack propagation along lamellar boundaries, dissipating energy."
        }
      ],
      "interface_notes": [
        {
          "stress_strain_distribution": "Stress concentration at crack tip in δ-ferrite lamellae is relieved by interface separation in carbide/ferrite lamellae."
        },
        {
          "slippage_situation": "Dislocation pile-up at carbide/ferrite interface due to Orowan mechanism; good interfacial incompatibility."
        }
      ],
      "phase_evolution": "During low-temperature rolling, supersaturated martensite decomposes, C, Cr, Mn enrich at defect sites, precipitating ultra-fine spherical carbides (M3C, M23C6, M7C3) within ferrite matrix; carbides grow by Ostwald ripening with increasing temperature."
    },
